## load taxonomy from https://arxiv.org/category_taxonomy
website_url = requests.get('https://arxiv.org/category_taxonomy').text
soup = BeautifulSoup(website_url,'html.parser')

root = soup.find('div',{'id':'category_taxonomy_list'})

tags = root.find_all(["h2","h3","h4","p"], recursive=True)

data = []

level_1_name = ""
level_2_code = ""
level_2_name = ""
level_3_code = ""
level_3_name = ""

for t in tags:
    if t.name == "h2":
        level_1_name = t.text
        level_2_code = t.text
        level_2_name = t.text
    elif t.name == "h3":
        raw = t.text
        level_2_code = re.sub(r"(.*)\((.*)\)", r"\2", raw)
        level_2_name = re.sub(r"(.*)\((.*)\)", r"\1", raw)
    elif t.name == "h4":
        raw = t.text
        level_3_code = re.sub(r"(.*) \((.*)\)", r"\1", raw)
        level_3_name = re.sub(r"(.*) \((.*)\)", r"\2", raw)
    elif t.name == "p":
        notes = t.text
        data.append((level_1_name, level_2_name, level_2_code, level_3_name, level_3_code, notes))

schema = ["group_name", "archive_name", "archive_id", "category_name", "category_id", "category_description"]
taxonomy_df = spark.createDataFrame(data, schema=schema)

taxonomy_df.show(truncate=True)

# Eliminate stop words and special characters
@udf(StringType())
def remove_special_characters(data):
    cleaned_data = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]', ' ', data)
    return cleaned_data

def clean_data(df, column):
  cleaned_df = df.select(column);
  cleaned_df = df.withColumn(column, remove_special_characters(cleaned_df[column]))
  return cleaned_df
In[32]:
# Tokenize the dataframe
@udf(ArrayType(StringType()))
def filter_words(words):
    return [word for word in words if word]

def tokenize(df, column):
  tokenizer = Tokenizer(inputCol=column, outputCol="words")
  tokenized_df = tokenizer.transform(df)
  tokenized_df = tokenized_df.withColumn("words", filter_words(tokenized_df["words"]))
  return tokenized_df
In[33]:
# Extract the keywords from tokenized dataframe
@udf(ArrayType(StringType()))
def extract_keyword(tokenized_words):
    keywordList = []
    for text in tokenized_words:
        r = Rake()
        r.extract_keywords_from_text(text)
        rankedList = r.get_ranked_phrases_with_scores()
        for keyword in rankedList:
            keyword_updated = keyword[1].split()
            if not (any(char.isdigit() for char in keyword_updated[0]) or len(keyword_updated[0]) == 1):
                keyword_updated_string = " ".join(keyword_updated[:2])
                keywordList.append(keyword_updated_string)
            if len(keywordList) > 9:
                break

    return keywordList

def keywords(df):
  keywords_df = df.withColumn("words", extract_keyword(df["words"]))
  return keywords_df

# Lemmatize the title words
nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_sm")

@udf(ArrayType(StringType()))
def lemmatize_text(words):
    doc = nlp(" ".join(words))
    lemmatized_words = [token.lemma_ for token in doc]
    return lemmatized_words

def lemmatize(df):
  lemmatized_df = df.withColumn("words", lemmatize_text(df["words"]))
  return lemmatized_df
In[35]:
# Vectorize our data with CountVectorizer(term frequency)
def vectorize(df):
  tfizer = CountVectorizer(inputCol='words', outputCol='tf_features')
  tf_model = tfizer.fit(df)
  tf_result = tf_model.transform(df)
  return tf_model, tf_result
In[36]:
# Use IDF(inverse document frequency) for score our words
def idf(df, column):
  idfizer = IDF(inputCol='tf_features', outputCol='tf_idf_features')
  idf_model = idfizer.fit(df)
  tfidf_result = idf_model.transform(df)
  return tfidf_result
In[37]:
# Model topics with LDA(Latent Dirichlet Allocation) algorithm
def lda_modeling(df, num_topics, max_iter):
  lda = LDA(k=num_topics, maxIter=max_iter, featuresCol='tf_idf_features')
  lda_model = lda.fit(df)
  return lda_model
In[38]:
def topic_extraction(column, num_topic, num_iter, range_df):
    column_df = reduced_df.limit(range_df)
    column_df = clean_data(column_df, column)
    column_df = tokenize(column_df, column)
    column_df = keywords(column_df)
    column_df = lemmatize(column_df)
    # column_df.select('words', 'group_name').show(truncate=100)
    
    # Top 10 most used words in all titles
    counts = column_df.select(explode('words').alias('word')).groupBy('word').count().collect()
    counts_df = spark.createDataFrame(counts)
    top_10_words = counts_df.orderBy(desc('count')).limit(10)
    top_10_words.show()
    
    topics_per_category = column_df.select('group_name').distinct().rdd.flatMap(lambda x: x).collect()
    for category in topics_per_category:
        print("Topic Extraction for " + str(category))
        category_df = column_df.filter(column_df.group_name == category)
        
        # Execute LDA per category
        tf_model, tf_result = vectorize(category_df)
        tfidf_result = idf(tf_result, column)
        lda_model = lda_modeling(tfidf_result, num_topic, num_iter)
        
        vocab = tf_model.vocabulary

        def get_words(token_list):
            return [vocab[token_id] for token_id in token_list]
    
        udf_to_words = udf(get_words, ArrayType(StringType()))
        topics = lda_model.describeTopics().withColumn('topicWords', udf_to_words(col('termIndices')))
        topics.select('topic', 'topicWords').show(truncate=False)

        def get_most_relevant_word(topicWords, termWeights):
            max_index = max(range(len(topicWords)), default=None, key=termWeights.__getitem__)
            return topicWords[max_index], termWeights[max_index]
        
        get_most_relevant_word_udf = udf(get_most_relevant_word, StructType([
            StructField("Words", StringType(), False),
            StructField("Weights", DoubleType(), False)
        ]))
        
        relevant_words_df = topics.withColumn("MostRelevant", get_most_relevant_word_udf("topicWords", "termWeights"))
        relevant_words_df = relevant_words_df.select("topic", "MostRelevant.Words", "MostRelevant.Weights")
        relevant_words_df.show(truncate=False)

# Define a UDF to compute cosine similarity
@udf(DoubleType())
def cosine_similarity_udf(embedding1, embedding2):
    # Convert embedding to DenseVector if they are lists
    if isinstance(embedding1, list):
        embedding1 = Vectors.dense(embedding1)
    if isinstance(embedding2, list):
        embedding2 = Vectors.dense(embedding2)

    return float(embedding1.dot(embedding2) / (embedding1.norm(2) * embedding2.norm(2)))

first_10_rows = reduced_df.take(10)

    ordered_df = ordered_df.orderBy("cosine_similarity", ascending=False)
    
    k = 10
    nearest_neighbors = ordered_df.limit(k).select("cosine_similarity", "id", "group_name", "title")
